args: No, it isn't. It looks as though we'll be\ncelebrating a dry Dragonyule this year.
No fair! It's not Dragonyule without\nsnow! This is the worst holiday EVER!
We can't control the weather, dear.
Hey! Where are you going, Lily?! LILY!
You gave me a start there, Lily.\nWhat's this all of a sudden?
Um, I'd like to borrow a dragon!
What in the world for, Lily?
I'll tell you! Here, listen.\n*whisper whisper*
Midgardsormr, I'm leaving everything in\nyour hands tonight. Er, claws.
Verily. Hold on tight. We are off!
We're almost right above the village.\nYou ready, Lily?
Yeah. I picked tons of cute little flowers,\nso we'll take them, and...
Freeze them...and let them fall,\njust like snow! Sprinkle sprinkle!
Wait, this isn't snow.\nThey're little flowers!
You're right. What a marvelous thing!
Mom! Now there's PRESENTS coming\nfrom the sky!
It's a Dragonyule miracle! Huh, Mom?
Right you are, sweetie. Right you are.
Flower snow and presents...\nYou think they're all happy with it?
I'm sure they are. Lookâ€”there are lights\nall over, illuminating the darkened village.
I'm sure they're all looking up into the\nsky right about now.
There was a child in town today who was\nheartbroken to hear there wouldn't be any\nsnow falling tonight.
And I... I just hate the idea of anyone\nbeing sad like that.
That's why I wondered if there might\nbe something I could do about it.
That's when I remembered how happy\neveryone was that time I gave them all\nice flowers!
Oh yeah. I do recall that.
Taking their sorrow and turning it into\nbeautiful, sparkling happiness...
Now that's a gift I knew I could give!
Oh, and Victor taught me how to do the\nparachute presents. Hee hee.
(Wielding her experience to benefit\nothers... Lily sure has grown.)
(She's not just a child waiting for gifts.\nShe's a young woman whose kind heart\ncompels her to give back.)
Do you think I've done a good job?\nDo you think they feel the holiday spirit?
I just want to give back to others what\nSaint Starfall gave to me back then.
You've done more than good. You've done\namazing tonight, Saint Starfall Lily.
